data.name: Instructions
data.value: Use this page to set up profile properties that can be used to store unique values for every visitor to your site. You can use profile properties to personalize your site for each user. ASP.NET stores profile property values in a database and makes them available to your application. You can choose to store profile property values for anonymous users as well as for users who are logged in to your site.

data.value: Create, edit, or delete profile property groups.

data.name: ManagePropertiesLinkText
data.value: Edit or delete existing profile properties.

data.value: A profile has not been enabled for this Web site.

data.value: Delete profile property values that have not been used since a specified date.
